###Apache Spark on Amazon EMR with Apache Zeppelin 

Below example will help you to explore how you can use [Spark Dataframe](http://spark.apache.org/docs/1.5.0/sql-programming-guide.html#dataframes) and how quickly you can start processing data using Spark on Amazon EMR. 
The given parquet format data ( originally CSV ) comes from the Department of Transportation : "[Public data set outlining flight information since 1987](https://catalog.data.gov/dataset/airline-on-time-performance-and-causes-of-flight-delays)".
The data set is around 4GB compressed ( 79GB uncompressed ) and contains 162,212,419 rows, so it makes sense to use a distriubuted framework like Spark for querying.

In this example, we can get below information.

* The 10 airports with the most departures.
* The most flight delays over 15 minutes.
* The most flight delays over 60 minutes.
* The most flight cancellations. 
* The number of flight cancellations by yearly quarter. 
* The 10 most popular flight routes.

This data is located in `US East region`, so please note that you must have launched your EMR cluster on `US East region`.

For more information about this example, refer to [here](https://aws.amazon.com/ko/blogs/aws/new-apache-spark-on-amazon-emr/).

####Let's get started !

paragraphs.title: Analytics With Spark â€“ A Quick Example
paragraphs.text:
val parquetFile = sqlContext.parquetFile("s3://us-east-1.elasticmapreduce.samples/flightdata/input/")
parquetFile.registerTempTable("flights")

//1. Top 10 airports with the most departures since 2000
val topDepartures = sqlc.table("flights")
    .filter($"year" >= 2000)
    .groupBy($"origin")
    .agg(count($"*").as("total_departures"))
    .orderBy($"total_departures")
    .sort($"total_departures".desc)
    .limit(10)

//2. Top 10 airports with the most departure delays over 15 minutes since 2000
val shortDepDelay = sqlc.table("flights")
    .filter($"depDelay" >= 15 && $"year" >= 2000)
    .groupBy($"origin")
    .agg(count($"depDelay").as("cnt"))
    .orderBy($"cnt")
    .sort($"cnt".desc)
    .limit(10)

//3. Top 10 airports with the most departure delays over 60 minutes since 2000
val longDepDelay = sqlc.table("flights")
    .filter($"depDelay" > 60 && $"year" >= 2000)
    .groupBy($"origin")
    .agg(count($"depDelay").as("total_delays"))
    .orderBy($"total_delays")
    .sort($"total_delays".desc)
    .limit(10)

//4. Top 10 airports with the most departure cancellations since 2000
val topCancel = sqlc.table("flights")
    .filter($"cancelled" === 1 && $"year" >= 2000)
    .groupBy($"origin")
    .agg(count($"cancelled").as("total_cancellations"))
    .orderBy($"total_cancellations")
    .sort($"total_cancellations".desc)
    .limit(10)

//5. Rank of the worst quarter of the year for departure cancellations
val quarterCancel = sqlc.table("flights")
    .filter($"cancelled" === 1)
    .groupBy($"quarter")
    .agg(count($"cancelled").as("total_cancellations"))
    .orderBy($"total_cancellations")
    .sort($"total_cancellations".desc)
    .limit(10)

//6. Top 10 most popular flight routes since 2000
val popularFlights = sqlc.table("flights")
    .filter($"year" >= 2000)
    .groupBy($"origin", $"dest")
    .agg(count($"*").as("total_flights"))
    .orderBy($"total_flights")
    .sort($"total_flights".desc)
    .limit(10)
